vulnerability.name: USN-6841-2
vulnerability.description: USN-6841-1 fixed a vulnerability in PHP. This update provides the corresponding updates for Ubuntu 16.04 LTS and Ubuntu 18.04 LTS.  Original advisory details:   It was discovered that PHP could early return in the filter_var function  resulting in invalid user information being treated as valid user  information. An attacker could possibly use this issue to expose raw  user input information.

statements.status_notes: PHP could be made to accept invalid URLs. Available with Ubuntu Pro.
